FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000000>Author</FONT><B></TD><TD valign=top><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000000>Comment</FONT><B></FONT></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2f2f4f><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uceleroy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Celeroy</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>ezOP</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>9/24/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>2:14:04 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=237.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Composite Bow Quest</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Ever since this quest has come online, I have been slobbering for at least one of our archers to wield one of these fine weapons. For one reason or another, we still don't have any. I would like to see us have two actually.<br>
<br>
To this end, I would like to call upon everyone to get around and lets get the equipment we need...make this a priority is what I am asking for.<br>
<br>
Dia and Crow, we need to know what all is left to buy, borrow or beat up to complete this quest!<br>
<br>
Tonight I ran across a melee guy that had 2 greater horns for sale and I bought them. That gives us three horns for sure that I know of. We have a ton of sinews for cooking. Dia I know is out there popping drudge Rav's for guts....I'm obliged to go along whenever we get online together. What else? <br>
<br>
LETS DO THIS THING!</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#6B8E23><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Crow</FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Unregistered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>9/24/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>10:13:21 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=237.topic&index=1><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Well...actually...</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Yesterday Dia was asking me about the quest. She had all the items except 1 horn. So, I gave her mine seeing as I still had tons of stuff to get. She now has all the parts to make a bow and is on her way to AB to get the horns shaped sometime today. Can't wait for her to get that bow!!</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2f2f4f><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uceleroy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Celeroy</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>ezOP</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>9/24/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>1:07:53 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=237.topic&index=2><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Well...actually...</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">YES! Woooo-Hoooo!<br>
<br>
Now we have two more horns Crow, what else for yours? <br>
<br>
C'MON, LETS DO THIS THING!</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#6B8E23><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/bforgottentruthforeignlegion.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dia>Dia</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>9/25/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>9:32:28 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=237.topic&index=3><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Composite bow ; The story</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Thanks to Crow, who gave me the last piece I needed, I now have the medium composite bow. Yes, medium. But it's still a very fine weapon that fits perfectly my actual level.<br>
<br>
Here are the stats:<br>
<br>
90% damage mod.<br>
+6% to melee defence ( +17% when I cast defender IV on it!)<br>
+4% to attack<br>
Bow mastery IV and BD IV ( req: arcane 140 + bow skill 210)<br>
speed 35<br>
<br>
Now for the yesterday's step by step story:<br>
<br>
It was a long run to Ayen Baqur, the far-west town of the Direlands. I first ran to Sylfear Dungeon (11,0N-14,7E) near Al-Jalima for its portal near the buttom. In the dungeon, take the first left and run straight (or what looks like the most straith path) till you get to the broken lifestone. Turn right, go down and pass an unlocked door. You will have to fight 1 shadow child, 2 shadows and 2 shadow lieutenants. Cross this room, go up, 2 more shadows and there is the portal behind an unlocked gate. The portal is level 21 restricted and cannot be linked to. It will portal you in mid-south direland at 88,3S-64,5W just beside a lifestone.<br>
<br>
Run south 2 km (no problem here) to a potal at 90,2S-64,5W. The portal is level 23 restricted and cannot be tied to. It drops you 78,7S-73,9W, near the Obsidian Rim. I chose to run as long as possible in the Rim. The fauna in there is light but the montains slows you down a bit. At a moment, I had to leave the safety of the Rim to sprint through virindis, golden wasps, skelton bone lords and knights and made it to Ayen Baqur loaded with all the debuffs possible I've collected on the way.<br>
<br>
I gave my 2 mattekar's horns to Yuan Hanzu to get them shaped. I also gave him my 2 fire auroch's horn and end up loosing them. Crow told me later that for auroch's horn, you must go to stonehold. Well, can't win them all.<br>
<br>
Then I used my shaped horns on cured large sinews. (It took me 8 large sinews to get 2 expertly cured large sinew with a cooking skill of 154.) Then put the 2 arms together to get a composite shaft. The sinew are for the speed of the bow. Expertly cook large sinews give a speed of 35, cured sinew gives 40 and small sinew gives 45. (Note that you cannot mix 2 kinds of sinew.)<br>
<br>
Then was the time to put the string on the shaft. My sting came from 3 Sclavus tongs liberatly oiled with blooddrinker oil. (7 attempts with alchemy at 162) My bow skill was 230 buffed and it gave me a dammage mod. of 90%. For a 110%, you will need a liberatly oiled sting from ravener's gut. It is said that you will need a bow skill of 280 to get a fair chance to string your bow with that kind of string. Thats why I chose to go for the 90% one.<br>
<br>
Last thing, put the handle on the shaft. It was carved from a lich bone. Took me 4 attempts to intric... well, to get it right. (fletching at 182). The handel gives a +4 attack, bow mastery 4 and bd 4 and the 140 diff and 210 bow skill requirements. Uses 1 mana per 20 sec. and can hold up to 500.<br>
<br>
Found no portal to link to near Ayen Baqur, but I am linked with the lifestone there and will still be for a few days.<br>
<br>
So I gave this bow a spin and was very pleased about it, more than anything, I appreciate the melee def. bonus. Got a Rav. gut, that I will give to Crow, who has been kind enough to give me his only horn. I will still be hunting great mattis and raveners to help you guys get a bow of your own.<br>
</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2f2f4f><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ugharadin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gharadin</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>9/25/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>12:09:52 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=237.topic&index=4><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Composite Bow Quest</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Wow, Dia, congratulations on a great quest for a fine weapon!!! Yikes, that sounds like it was quite a quite a run to Ayen Baqur, but it sure looks like the bow was worth it.  Great post, thanks for the description! I've been hunting outside in the Qal mountains lately just for a fun change of scenery after all that time I spent in the Citadel, hopefully I'll be able to find a horn or two to help out.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#6B8E23><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uceleroy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Celeroy</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>ezOP</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>9/25/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>1:04:06 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenF